Thirty-fifth Ave. (across line of trees in the foreground when constructed), north side, between 93rd Street (left) and Junction Boulevard (right). 94th Street if extended, will cut through the house. This is a set of four views, looking north, showing the Charles P. Leverich house from 1852-1891. It was subsequently owned by H.S. Leverich and the heirs of Chas. P. Leverich. In 1909 the property belonged to Chas. D. Leverich. All buildings seen in these views were demolished in June 1928.

March 1923.
View 2: March 1924.
Views & 4: March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
